{"modified": "2014-12-01T19:05:05", "description": "A list of GiottoJS examples", "name": "brush", "site": {"media": "/media", "python_version": "3.4.2", "url": "http://giottojs.org", "year": 2014, "template_engine": null, "date": "2014-12-18T14-30-26", "name": "Lux", "lux_version": "0.1.2-alpha.1", "template": "partials/examples.html"}, "html_url": "http://giottojs.org/examples/brush", "api_url": "http://giottojs.org/ng/examples/brush.json", "title": "Brushes", "head": {"description": "A list of GiottoJS examples", "title": "Brushes", "twitter:card": "summary_large_image"}, "date": "2014-12-01T00:00:00", "slug": "brush", "content_type": "text/html", "html": {"main": "<div id=\"page-main\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\" data-highlight>\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<h2>Brushes</h2>\n</div>\n<p>An example on how to use d3 brushes in giotto.</p>\n<h3>Javascript code</h3>\n<pre><code>gexamples.brush1 = {\n    height: '20%',\n\n    css: {\n        selected: {\n            stroke: '#444',\n            'stroke-width': '1.5px'\n        }\n    },\n\n    yaxis: {\n        show: false,\n        min: 0,\n        max: 1\n    },\n\n    brush: {\n        extent: [0.4, 0.6]\n    },\n\n    data: function (chart) {\n        var norm = d3.random.normal(0.5, 0.1);\n        return [{\n            line: {show: false},\n            point: {\n                show: true,\n                width: 0\n            },\n            data: d3.range(800).map(function () {\n                return [Math.random(), norm()];\n            })\n        }];\n    }\n};\n</code></pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<script>\n\n    gexamples.brush1 = {\n        height: '20%',\n\n        css: {\n            selected: {\n                stroke: '#444',\n                'stroke-width': '1.5px'\n            }\n        },\n\n        yaxis: {\n            show: false,\n            min: 0,\n            max: 1\n        },\n\n        brush: {\n            extent: [0.4, 0.6]\n        },\n\n        data: function (chart) {\n            var norm = d3.random.normal(0.5, 0.1);\n            return [{\n                line: {show: false},\n                point: {\n                    show: true,\n                    width: 0\n                },\n                data: d3.range(800).map(function () {\n                    return [Math.random(), norm()];\n                })\n            }];\n        }\n    };\n\n</script>\n<div id=\"footer\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 small\">\n<p>Library released under the <a href=\"http://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause\">BSD License</a>.</p>\n<p>Copyright 2014 <a href=\"http://lucasbardella.com\">Luca Sbardella</a> and <a href=\"http://quantmind.com\">Quantmind</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}}